    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-03-27T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-03-27T19:00:00-05:00" n="518"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d518">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.00/1294b</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Gonzales</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-03-27T19:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 27, 1917—7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Commander <hi rend="italic">Prairie</hi> reports food shortage in Guantanamo City
                    becoming serious and considers that the reinstatement of federal customs and
                    postal officials and the opening of the port an immediate necessity. He also
                    stated that in the absence of instructions to the contrary the federal officials
                    will be reinstated and protected.</p>
                <p>You will take this up with the Cuban Government and report.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
